{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φλόξ</b>, ἡ, <br /> <i>genitive</i> φλογός: (φλέγω):— <b>flame</b> of fire, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.71, etc.; δεινὴ δὲ φλὸξ ὦρτο θεείου καιομένοιο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.135; τῆς δὲ [νηὸς] κατ᾽ ἀσβέστη κέχυτο φλόξ 16.123; κατὰ πῦρ ἐκάη καὶ φλὸξ ἐμαράνθη 9.212; more fully, φλὸξ Ἡφαίστοιο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.88, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” [same place]; πυρός 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.225, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 8, “Heracl.” 914 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 83b, etc. (but also φλογὸς αἰθέριον πῦρ 4th-5th c.BC: Parmenides Poeta Philosophus 8.56)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φλογὸς σπέρμα, of live charcoal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.48 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀναιθύσσειν, θύειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 344, “IT” 1331 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐγείρειν, παρακαλεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.24, “Cyr.” 7.5.23; ἐμβαλεῖν τινι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 4, “Rh.” 120; σβέσαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.77; φ. ἀπέσσυτο 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 859; ἀπορρέουσα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 67c; φλογὸς ἀποσβεσθείσης [prev. work] 58c \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: later in <i>plural</i>, <b>flames, meteors,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 341b2, “Mu.” 392b3, 400a30, 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Lithica” 178, 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “fragment” 74.48. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>fire</b> as an element, φλογὸς αἶσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Parmenides Poeta Philosophus 12.2; φ. ἱλάειρα 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 85. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of other kinds of <b>flame,</b> φ. κεραυνία, οὐρανία, of lightning, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1017, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 144 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the <b>heat</b> of the sun, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 22, “Pers.” 505, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 696 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>flash</b> of a miraculous cloud, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.206 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of precious stones, ψυχρὰ φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 123.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; the <b>blade</b> of a sword, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Josh.3.22, 2nd c.AD: Aquila LXX, 2nd c.AD(?): Theodotion LXX.1Ki.17.7. \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> in similes and metaphors, φλογὶ εἴκελος, ἶσος, of <b>fiery</b> warriors, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.330, 39 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φ. οἴνου <b>the fiery strength</b> of wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 758; φ. πήματος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 166 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wallflower, Cheiranthus Cheiri,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 6.6.2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5395","accentedUnicode":"φλόξ","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5394","matchingForm":"φλογίζω","stepTransliteration":"flogizō","gloss":"to kindle","_zh_tw_Gloss":"點燃","_es_Gloss":"encender","_zh_Gloss":"点燃"}],"shortDef":"flame, blaze","mediumDef":"<b>a flame, blaze</b> <ref='Luk.16.24'>Lk. 16:24</ref>; <ref='Act.7.30'>Acts 7:30</ref>","stepGloss":"flame","stepTransliteration":"flox","cou